I'm afraid that I would not have much to contribute to your questions. But, I suspect that Art and you are correct that alcohol was more of a probem than drugs, that the military services outlook on alcohol abused was liberal. Access to alcohol to myself was on log days, we each got two cans of beer(3.2% alcohol content) and two cans of Coca Cola. Always traded the beer for soda. On the rare times we pulled security for a new FB (consisted of filling sandbags &amp; perimeter guard)tiger piss was available, but not many drank the stuff. I left the field three days before catching the freedom bird, and at the Battalion aid station, it was used as an excuse to party. With the numbers rotating in and out, they lacked not very many nights were the had an excuse to ply themselves with booze.
